entries.femaleVariant: Now, I may not be good with names, but I do have quite the talent for faces!
Very unlikely.
V, so nice to see you.
So tell me. And mark well I still have my phone at hand.
Parade in Japantown – we need intel.
Need intel on the parade that's scheduled to come through Japantown.
So it's Arasaka... again.
What I fail to understand is... why come to me?
Did Mr. DeShawn not come to the phone?
That's it, it's all I have.
It must be enough.
Then go, be on your way.
Not at all curious what we're going to all this trouble for?
We appreciate this, Okada-san.
Where have I seen yours before? On the TV...?
Ah. You are just in time.
V? We should go in. Now.
OK, let's go.
Hideshi, don't leave this poor guy hangin'.
Hideshi, don't leave this poor guy hangin'.
This is not the best time, truly.
Oh, come on! I haven't heard it in years!
Fine, let's go.
This information... it could be just what we need.
But I will try to investigate further. I will stay here some time and call some associates.
The moment I learn something new, I will let you know.
I beg your pardon?
You look like a man whose last best hope is a stroke of good fortune.
You truly think so?
Fortune is like a roulette wheel. Sometimes all it takes is a little push. A risk.
Let's start with your debt to me – for the Sandra Dorsett job.
Let's start with the eddies you already owe me – Sandra Dorsett job?
Weren't in any rush to collect before. Surely you can wait a little longer.
V, now is not the time. Tell Okada-san what we come for.
That was close. He almost recognized me.
A delightful, mature woman.
Everything's on the shards.
Japantown.
Whole district is to be sealed off for the parade.
Dashi platforms, the main attraction. They'll fly this way, high above street level.
Hanako Arasaka, the guest of honor, will deliver her speech from the largest float. She'll do this exactly… here.
Got no idea about security, but given recent... events, expect it to be tight.
Our last parade? Arasaka undercovers infiltrated the crowd.
Not to mention a smattering of sharpshooters, drones. And if that's not enough fun for one day, a netrunner, one at least.
At the end, the floats will float out of Japantown, and we'll be left with trash up to our elbows that no one will collect.
[Take shard]
Rogue, my sweet, this has got to be a misunderstanding…
I've no idea who jumped your team, but the Claws – no, never. My boys know their place.
I-I'm sorry, got to go. I have... guests.
And your charming friend is...?
Workin' together.
Hideshi Hino – comedian.
Happen to be workin' together, that's all.
Hideshi Hino – the comedian.
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="タケムラ・ゴロウです。オカダさん、お会いできて光栄です" t="Goro Takemura. The honor is mine, Okada-san." b="" a=""/>
Haaa... a true gentleman!
Shame, only, that he's being hunted by all Arasaka's tin soldiers.
And you, V, bring him to my door.
Gimme one reason why I shouldn't notify the proper "authorities" right away.
We come with biz, and you love to make eddies.
Simple. You're damned curious.
Would've already made the call if you intended to.
Simple – you're curious to see what we got.
Eddies is why. Always about eddies, Wakako.
You wanna make 'em – we got biz. Doesn't get any simpler.
Risk's too high. They might think you're involved.
Caution.
Caution?
World's most wanted Japanese fugitive's hidin' out in Night City and you got nothin' to do with it? Please…
We know their thinkin'. They'll link you to us faster than you can finish puffin' on that cig.
You know everything that goes on this 'hood.
Heard Arasaka killed your grandkid.
Goro, why's Dex not available – remind me?
Goro? Remind me why Dex's fat, backstabbing ass is currently indisposed?
He is deceased.
Butchered and dumped at a landfill by some Arasaka goon. Real shame, that.
Arasaka, Tyger Claws – kinda like the family dog screwin' the cat, hm?
entries.maleVariant: Arasaka, Tyger Claws – kinda like the family dog screwin' the cat, huh?

entries.femaleVariant: C'mon, got your finger on the 'hood's pulse, know everything.
That a threat I detect?
Just the facts – nothin' more.
No threat, no. Asked why I couldn't reach Dex, I answered. Just facts, nothin' more.
It is no threat, of course!
Okada-san, our intentions are honorable. We need just information. It is a matter of life and death.
Parade honoring Saburo Arasaka? You're preppin' in some way, no doubt.
Can't possibly be fond of the people who killed your grandkid.
That was very long ago.
Time's the best healer? Wound like that, though…
A wound like that, no.
But of course! Hideshi Hino, the man, the legend – in the flesh!
Do you know who this is? Hideshi Hino! The late-night comedy host! He was brilliant before he fell off the wagon!
But… a comedian?!
Egh...
BETTER BUCKLE UP!
Wow...
Hino-san... what happened to you?
Can you still do your famous, "BETTER BUCKLE UP!"
Come on, you don't forget a thing like that! Just once, please?
No.
I do not know. I do not recognize myself.
Hideshi Hino... To have fallen so far... Such a shame...
Are you happy? May we go?
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="やめろって言ってんだ" t="Stop it, asshole." b="" a=""/>
V? Whatever you're planning against Arasaka... this time, do it right.
Well, well! Have you tried your luck at the slots?
With your sense of humor, why not?
Stay safe.
Keep a low profile.
Stay safe, Goro.
Just... low profile, OK? Don't start handing out autographs.
You as well. Until next time.
In fame, I could not overtake you if I tried. Be safe, V.
Thanks, Wakako.
Not at all curious what we're after?
Blissful ignorance has served me well. In any case... I'll find out soon, won't I?
Thanks, Wakako.
They use the city CCTV to observe everything. Main access point – here, it's an old, automated control center. If you ask me, most useful by far.
Along the parade route – balconies, footbridges and vantage points affording good views.
Won't see me dressed in mourning…
<kiroshi l="jpn" o="いま何て？" t="Come again?" b="" a=""/>
But the rest is true.
For free? You sure?
Got my reasons. But patience I got none.
How much does this cost? My pockets... are empty.
Clearly.
My gift to you, it's free.
Okada-san... what is free often proves most costly.
Gonna take them or not?
Good, 'cause you would then have to join him.
Mmm... How I missed the sound.
Hmm... Perhaps... Perhaps you have a point. I appreciate this advice.
[Get out]
Free? You sure?
